<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 09 at 12:46AM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...SLICK SPOTS POSSIBLE INTO THE MORNING COMMUTE...
Temperatures are expected to fall into the mid 20s to around 30
through the remainder of the overnight. Any wet pavement due to
recent rain or melted snow on sidewalks or roadways may re-freeze
into black ice as temperatures continue to fall. Secondary and
side roads as well as shaded areas are most vulnerable to black
ice.
Motorists should assume that pavement which looks wet could be icy
and to proceed with caution.</description>
